    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54B32 inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies and Double VANOS variable valve timing. This example is mechanically pristine, with documented rod bearing replacement and a fully reinforced rear subframe to ensure long-term structural rigidity. The Getrag 6-speed manual transmission shifts with clinical precision, paired with a factory-spec variable M-differential lock for optimal power delivery. The suspension retains its original geometry with fresh bushings and dampers, providing the signature tactile feedback and neutral handling balance the chassis is celebrated for. This is a turn-key, collector-quality specimen for the purist who demands mechanical transparency.",
